In [87]:
#categorizing production levels
def quan(x):
    if x > 2425 :
        return 'High'
    else:
        return 'Low'
df['Production'] = df['quantity'].apply(quan)
#df['rate'] = np.where( df['quantity'] > 5000 ,'high production','low production')  #create column for high/low if production more than 2425

axes[1,1].set_title('Total Amount of Quantity Per Destination')

plt.tight_layout(pad=2)
